In theory you could achieve this with:
assertEquals(blogger1, adapter.query(BlogOwner.class, blogger1.getId()).get(0));

But that gets kind of long, and loses the DAMP you have.
Maybe:
assertRecordIsInDB(BlogOwner.class, blogger1.getId());

To use the same type of arguments as the storage interface usually do, though?
private <T extends Model> void assertRecordIsInDB(T item) {
    List<T> results = adapter.query(item.getClass(), item.getId());
    assertEquals(1, results.size());
    assertEquals(item, results.get(0));
}

